<subSubSection id="C32D6512C04AED46BA8EF98A9C0920D9" pageId="1" pageNumber="248" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B883699C04AED46BA8EF98A9C0920D9" blockId="1.[226,1361,1609,1784]" pageId="1" pageNumber="248">
Comment: According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA64B68C04AED46B8E9F98A9D082044" author="SMETANA A" box="[645,872,1609,1637]" pageId="1" pageNumber="248" pagination="579 - 624" refId="ref9311" refString="SMETANA A. (2004): Subfamily Paederinae FLEMING, 1821. - In: LOBL I. &amp; A. SMETANA (eds), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Volume 2. Hydrophiloidea - Histeroidea - Staphylinoidea. - Apollo Books, Stenstrup: 579 - 624." type="book chapter" year="2004">SMETANA (2004)</bibRefCitation>
, this species has a trans-Palaearctic distribution. However, reliably identified material from the East Palaearctic region east of Middle Asia is unknown to me. In Middle Asia, 
<taxonomicName id="4C374D1AC04AED46B919F9509A7B208E" baseAuthorityName="GRAVENHORST" baseAuthorityYear="1806" box="[885,1051,1683,1711]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvipenne">
<emphasis id="B943EA8BC04AED46B919F9509A7B208E" box="[885,1051,1683,1711]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="248">L. fulvipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="F3207609C04AED46BA8EF9749F1920F2" box="[226,377,1719,1747]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="1" pageNumber="248">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3207609C04AED46BBE3F9749C2220F2" box="[399,578,1719,1747]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="1" pageNumber="248">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F3207609C04AED46B8FAF9749D4920F2" box="[662,809,1719,1747]" name="Uzbekistan" pageId="1" pageNumber="248">Uzbekistan</collectingCountry>
. The above specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="F3207609C04AED46BED3F9749B3120F2" box="[1215,1361,1719,1747]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="1" pageNumber="248">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
represent new country records.
</paragraph>
